title: This week's top selling songs and albums on Apple's iTunes
text:
The Canadian Press - ONLINE EDITION This week's top selling songs and albums on Apple's iTunes By: The Associated Press 
iTunes' Official Music Charts for the week ending Oct. 1, 2015: 
Top Songs 
1. The Hills, The Weeknd 
2. Hotline Bling, Drake 
3. What Do You Mean?, Justin Bieber 
4. Wildest Dreams, Taylor Swift 
5. 679 (feat. Monty), Fetty Wap 
6. Locked Away (feat. Adam Levine), R. City 
7. Stitches, Shawn Mendes 
8. Downtown (feat. Eric Nally, Melle Mel, Kool Moe Dee & Grandmaster Caz) - Single, Macklemore & Ryan Lewis 
9. Can't Feel My Face, The Weeknd 
10. Writing's On the Wall, Sam Smith 
Top Albums 
1. What a Time To Be Alive, Drake & Future 
2. Fetty Wap , Fetty Wap 
3. Cold Beer Conversation, George Strait 
4. Tangled Up, Thomas Rhett 
5. T R A P S O U L, Bryson Tiller 
6. Beauty Behind the Madness, The Weeknd 
7. Hamilton (Original Broadway Cast Recording), Various Artists 
8. 1989, Ryan Adams 
10. Cass County , Don Henley
